01/05/2006
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- The interior ministry and the International Association of Chiefs of Police organised a two-day conference of European police chiefs that opened Monday (1 May) in Sofia.
Senior police officials from 15 European countries and the United States are participating in the event, which is aimed at strengthening co-operation in the security sector.
Closed-door discussions are expected to focus on enhancing collaboration against organised crime and money laundering, as well as boosting police work in multiethnic societies.
(Darik - 01/05/06;
BNR, Bulgarian Government Web site - 30/04/06)
